         <abstract>
            <p>The latest innovations in coordinate measuring machines and instrumentation have been combined with theoretical gear calculations to provide an objective quantitative method for inspecting bevel and hypoid gears. The measuring machine, its software, the gear software and the measuring procedure are described. Also included is an example of the use of the procedure in the development of a gear set.</p>
